name: Air Canada 777 and Edelweiss A330 Landing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Two of YYC's more interesting heavies arriving just after a heavy storm on runway 35L at the end of June. ATC is included for the 777, none for the 330 sadly. Enjoy this quick video!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFO
Airline: Air Canada (ACA/AC) and Edelweiss Air (EDW/WK)
Aircraft: Boeing 777-200LR (B77L) and A330-200 (A332)
Aircraft Name: AC - None, WK - Kiburi
Livery: Standard, Old
Engines: 2x GE90-110B1L and 2X PW4168A
Registration: C-FNNH and HB-IQI
Route: LHR-YYC, ZRH-YYC
Callsign: Air Canada 851 heavy, Edelweiss 14 heavy
Runway used: 35L
Local Time: 1500
